Interface TestResultObserver

All Known Implementing Classes:
TestResults
public interface TestResultObserver
The TestResultObserver interface defines a contract for objects that want to be notified of updates related to test results. The implementing classes will define how to handle the notification when a student's test results are updated, including the marks, feedback, and the test name.

This is typically used in an observer design pattern where the observer is notified about changes in test results, enabling dynamic updates in a system.
